                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.77a/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 15, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>351. Your 905, October 15, noon. Inasmuch as the appointment of a British
                    engineer-in-chief for the Hupeh-Hunan section of the Canton-Hankow Railway is
                    stipulated in Article 17 of the Hukuang Loan <pb facs="0708" n="610"
                        xml:id="pg_610"/> Agreement of May 20, 1911, to which the American group is
                    a party, you are authorized to join with the other interested Legations in
                    making identic or similar representations to the Chinese Government concerning
                    the execution of the provisions of the Loan Agreement with respect to the
                    present incumbent as well as concerning the employment of European and/or
                    American engineers-in-chief during the currency of the loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
